<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1058,1515]" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,1166,1191]" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Klautau, 2017" authorityName="Klautau" authorityYear="2017" box="[308,462,1167,1190]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Ernstia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="citrea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[308,462,1167,1190]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">Ernstia citrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[471,563,1166,1191]" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[471,563,1166,1191]" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a common species in Rocas Atoll. It was found from 
<quantity box="[1209,1327,1166,1191]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="325" unit="m" value="1.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5 to 3 m</quantity>
of depth, always in shaded areas, only partially exposed to sunlight. It occurs usually on vertical walls and on the ceilings of small crevices. 
<collectingRegion box="[324,358,1239,1262]" country="Haiti" name="Nord" pageId="24" pageNumber="325">No</collectingRegion>
macroscopic organisms were found associated with this species.
</paragraph>
